							<td><center><i class="orange female icon"></i></center></td>
							<td><center><i class="orange male icon"></i></center></td>
							<td><center><i class="orange female icon"></i></center></td>
						</tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
				<p>There are a few more male of female only, but that is basically it! Everywhere else in Ido, you'll see a really good system, where every single word is neutral (either sex, all of them togheter or non of them at all). Basically every noun ends in <i>o</i>, if you want to make the noun male; you add <i>ul</i> before the noun ending <i>o</i>, and to make the noun female; you add <i>in</i> before the noun ending <i>o</i>! It's that easy!</p>
				<table class="ui orange definition striped table">
					<tbody>
						<tr>
